    "discriminators": [
     "Sparse, irregular events: a bright inharmonic carabiner or piton clink, a gritty scuff of boot and hand on rock, rope running through gear, and breathy effort. Sparse and aperiodic is the contrast with SPORTS-EQUESTRIAN, whose hoofbeats are a fast periodic train.",
     "SPORTS-WINTER already claims 'Climbing' among its synonyms, which is really ice climbing and mountaineering. Snow and ice underfoot, crampons, a bright hissy ski or blade scrape — that stays WINTER. Bare rock, chalk, bouldering and gym walls come here. Both are legitimate; the surface named in the file decides.",
     "The component sounds all have homes of their own: the clink is METAL-IMPACT, the scrape is ROCKS-FRICTION, the rope is ROPE-MOVEMENT and the rack is EQUIPMENT-RECREATIONAL. Use this only when the climb is the subject."
    ],
