    "discriminators": [
     "Court sport: sharp ball and racket impacts inside a REVERBERANT hall, plus shoe squeak (a short, high-centroid friction chirp) and dribbling, which reads as a periodic onset train. The reverberant tail on each impact is the only reliable indoor cue, and it is shared with every other indoor sport.",
     "Be honest: a tennis hit and a baseball hit are the same physics — a sharp impulsive impact. DSP cannot separate SPORTS-COURT from SPORTS-FIELD. Only the sport named in the file (badminton, basketball, squash, volleyball) decides.",
     "The crowd bed, if present, is CROWDS-SPORT and the venue tone is AMBIENCE-SPORT; isolated shoe squeak is FOLEY-FEET."
    ],
