    "discriminators": [
     "The scene, not the animal. A periodic hoof onset train (a gallop is roughly 4 beats per stride, a trot 2) over a turf or sand bed, layered with tack jingle, rider efforts, a starting-gate clang and a crowd. The periodicity plus the damped, low-heavy thud of hoof on ground is the only signal cue, and it belongs to the hooves, not to the sport.",
     "Be honest: DSP cannot tell a race from a hack down a lane. Isolated hooves are FOOTSTEPS-HORSE, the whinny is ANIMALS-HORSE, and the saddle and bridle are EQUIPMENT-BRIDLE & TACK. This subcategory is earned only by the words — derby, dressage, polo, jockey, showjumping, steeplechase.",
