    "discriminators": [
     "The one SPORTS subcategory with a genuine, assertable morphology. Urethane wheels on concrete produce a SUSTAINED broadband rolling friction bed — noisy, unpitched, near-stationary, low-to-mid heavy — punctuated by hard wooden board slaps at take-off and landing.",
     "The roll is the discriminator against every impact-only sibling: SPORTS-COURT, FIELD, GYM and INDOOR are all onset trains with silence between. This one has a continuous floor of noise.",
     "SPORTS-WINTER's blade-on-ice scrape is the same idea but far BRIGHTER and hissier; the urethane rumble here is comparatively low and dark. The words skateboard, roller, inline and scooter pin it here, while ice, ski, snow and hockey pull it to WINTER."
    ],
